FT  19 NOV 94 / UK Company News: Chester Water
Chester Water reported pre-tax profits up from Pounds 1.07m to Pounds 1.23m
for the six months to September 30.
Turnover was Pounds 3.08m, compared with Pounds 3m.
Profits were helped by the lack of non-recurring costs of Pounds 159,000
relating to the financial reorganisation when the company gained plc status,
a further reduction in costs in the core business and an increase in income
from non-core activities.
Earnings per share were 7.3p (6.3p) and the interim dividend is 1.95p,
compared with 1.7p adjusted for the share sub-division.
